Name: VER_CMD_INV_DEST
Description: Failure code for all (1,10) reports

Name: VER_REP_CR_FD
Description: Failure code for start actions when they unsuccessfully attempt to create a new report from the OutFactory

Name: VER_OUTLOADER_FD
Description: Failure code for start actions when the Load operation in the OutLoader has failed

Name: VER_SID_IN_USE
Description: A (3,1) or (3,2) command attempted to create a new report with a SID which is already in use

Name: VER_FULL_RDL
Description: A (3,1) or (3,2) command attempted to create a new report at a time when the RDL is already full

Name: VER_RDL_CONSTR
Description: A (3,1) or (3,2) command attempted to create a new report which configuration data which violate an RDL constraint of table \ref{tab:repDefDataStruct}
verFailData: The identifier of the violated constraint

Name: VER_DUPL_DI
Description: A (3,1) or (3,2) command carried the same data item identifier twice

Name: VER_ILL_SID
Description: A service 3 command had an invalid SID

Name: VER_ENABLED_SID
Description: A (3,3) or (3,4) command attempted to enabled a SID which is already enabled

Name: VER_SID_START_FD
Description: All the instructions in a service 3 command have been rejected

Name: VER_FACT_PRGR_FD
Description: The progress action of a multi-instruction service 3 command has failed to retrieve a report from the OutFactory
verFailData: The SID for which the retrieval from the OutFactory was attempted

Name: VER_ILL_EID
Description: The start action of a service 5 command has encountered an illegal Event Identifier (EID)

Name: VER_EID_ST_FD
Description: All the instructions in a service 5 command have been rejected

Name: VER_ILL_MON
Description: A Parameter or Functional Monitor Identifier in a service 12 command is out-of-range or not defined
verFailData: The rejected Parameter or Functional Monitor Identifier

Name: VER_MON_START_FD
Description: All the instructions in a service 12 command have been rejected

Name: VER_PMDL_FULL
Description: A service 12 command has found the Parameter Monitor Definition List (PMDL) full
verFailData: The parameter monitor identifier for which the violation was found

Name: VER_MOD_ILL_DI
Description: A service 12 command has found the data item identifier of the parameter to be monitored illegal
verFailData: The parameter monitor identifier for which the violation was found

Name: VER_MON_PROT
Description: A service 12 command as found a parameter monitor which belongs to a protected functional monitor
verFailData: The parameter monitor identifier for which the violation was found

Name: VER_MON_ENB
Description: A service 12 command has found a parameter or functional monitor which is enabled
verFailData: The parameter or functional monitor identifier for which the violation was found

Name: VER_MON_USE
Description: A service 12 command has found a parameter monitor which is used by a functional monitor
verFailData: The parameter monitor identifier for which the violation was found

Name: VER_FMDL_FULL
Description: A service 12 command has found a Functional Monitor Definition List (FMDL) full
verFailData: The functional monitor identifier for which the violation was found

Name: VER_MON_TMP
Description: A service 12 command has found too many parameter monitors in a functional monitor
verFailData: The functional monitor identifier for which the violation was found

Name: VER_MON_MFN
Description: A service 12 command has found a value of minimum failing number equal to zero
verFailData: The functional monitor identifier for which the violation was found

Name: VER_SCD_ILL_SS
Description: Failure code for start action of service 11 command when it finds an illegal sub-schedule identifier

Name: VER_FULL_TBS
Description: A service 11 command found the Time-Based Schedule (TBS) full
verFailData: Identifier of the request within the command where the error occurred

Name: VER_SCD_ILL_G
Description: A service 11 command found an illegal schedule group identifier

Name: VER_SCD_ILL_RT
Description: A service 11 command found an illegal release time
verFailData: Coarse part of illegal release time

Name: VER_SCD_ILL_DS
Description: A service 11 command found an illegal destination for an scheduled command

Name: VER_SCD_CRFAIL
Description: A service 11 command was unable to create an InCommand for a scheduled command (either due to lack of resources or due to illegal command type)
verFailData: Identifier of the request within the command where the error occurred

Name: VER_SCD_ST_FD
Description: All instructions in a service 11 command have been rejected

Name: VER_ILL_ACT_ID
Description: Command (11,5) was unable to find an activity identifier in the TBS
verFailData: The sequence count part of the activity ID
